# Wavefoundry — Cursor Context

Thin pointer. Read `AGENTS.md` first for the full agent operating surface.

## Startup Order

1. Read `AGENTS.md` — shortcuts, stage gate, framework script hygiene, git commits policy
2. Read `docs/prompts/index.md` — public command catalog
3. Read `docs/agents/session-handoff.md` — current session state if work is in progress

## Key Guardrails

- Stage gate before any code edit: change doc → wave admission → Prepare wave
- Never commit without explicit operator instruction in the current session
- Seed edits require `seed_edit_allowed` guard approval
- Framework maintenance edits require `framework_edit_allowed` guard approval

## After File Edits

**Agents:** Prefer MCP **`wave_validate`** (and **`wave_garden`** when metadata needs refresh) over shelling out to docs launchers.

The `afterFileEdit` hook runs **`.wavefoundry/bin/docs-lint`** after any edit to `docs/`. Fix failures before continuing.
